title: Holly McNarland-Sour Pie EP, Canadian alt-rock
description:
This is a 1995 EP from this Canadian artist who took the 'angry women' genre from Alanis and distilled it into an even more vitriolic potion. Check out for instance her ode to premature ejaculation 'Mr 5 Minutes' and you just know these are not arbitrary lyrics. 

The recording has a very 'demo-ish' feel with sparse production resulting in a very clear, dynamic and full-ranged sound. I used it as a demo CD on some $30,000 speakers back in the 1990s and it rocked! The music and production are also excellent. I used to keep a few extra copies of this CD around, as almost invariably people who heard this wanted a copy for themselves
